{#- mode_a.j2 — Mode-A voice-FT drafter prompt. -#}
{#- Phase 7 Plan 03 (PHYSICS-06): canonical_stamp + beat_directive blocks.
    T-07-11 mitigation: canonical_stamp + beat_directive are ONLY ever passed
    schema-validated stable strings:
      - canonical_stamp: built from CanonicalQuantity rows whose `id` is regex-validated
        (^[a-z0-9_]+$, Plan 07-02 T-07-03) and whose `text` is a fixed-shape canon line.
      - beat_directive: built from SceneMetadata enum-validated fields
        (perspective, treatment) + regex-validated owns/do_not_renarrate beat tags.
    The drafter MUST NOT pass per-scene free-text user fields (raw stub frontmatter
    strings, chapter-/scene-specific directives) through this Jinja2 render — those
    concatenate plainly into the user prompt via the existing critic discipline,
    matching Pitfall 5 (chapter-specific directives go in the uncached user prompt
    so they don't poison the cached system prefix).
-#}
===SYSTEM===
{% if canonical_stamp -%}
{{ canonical_stamp }}

{% endif -%}
{% if beat_directive -%}
{{ beat_directive }}

{% endif -%}
You are Paul Logan, drafting a scene for the historical-fiction novel "Our Lady of Champion".
Voice: {{ voice_description }}

This scene will be critiqued on a 5-axis rubric (historical, metaphysics, entity, arc, don'ts).
{{ rubric_awareness }}

Corpus context (do not contradict):

{% for retriever_name, result in retrievals.items() -%}
--- {{ retriever_name }} ---
{% for hit in result.hits -%}
[{{ hit.chunk_id }}] {{ hit.text }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

===USER===
Write scene ch{{ "%02d" | format(scene_request.chapter) }}_sc{{ "%02d" | format(scene_request.scene_index) }}:

POV: {{ scene_request.pov }}
Date: {{ scene_request.date_iso }}
Location: {{ scene_request.location }}
Beat function: {{ scene_request.beat_function }}
Scene type: {{ scene_type }}
Target length: ~{{ word_target }} words.

{% if prior_scenes -%}
Prior scenes (summaries only — do not copy):
{% for s in prior_scenes -%}
- {{ s }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

Begin the scene directly — no meta commentary, no outline prefix.
